1 030/2024/05/9 Cabinet Paper for Fisheries Management and Conservation Plan Ricardo Benjamin Agriculture, Fisheries, Blue and Green Economy 06/05/2024
  1. Cabinet established a comprehensive regulatory framework to govern marine pollution prevention and control activities.
  2. Cabinet conducted a comprehensive assessment to identify major sources of marine pollution, including industrial discharges, agricultural runoff, sewage outfalls, and maritime activities.
  3. Cabinet developed and implemented pollution prevention strategies targeting key sources of marine pollution.
